.TH usbreset 8 "23 April 2019" "usbutils-VERSION" "Linux USB Utilities"
.IX usbreset
.SH NAME
usbreset \- reset USB devices
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B usbreset
[
.I options
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B usbreset
is a utility for resetting USB devices via the USBDEVFS_RESET ioctl.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B PPPP:VVVV
Tells
.I usbreset
to reset the USB device base on the given product and vendor ID (in hex).
.TP
.B BBB:DDD
Tells
.I usbreset
to reset the USB device base on the given bus and device number.
.TP
.B "Product"
Tells
.I usbreset
to reset the USB device base on the given product name.

.SH RETURN VALUE
If the specified device is not found, a non-zero exit code is returned.

.SH AUTHOR
Fabian Baumanis, <fabian.baumanis@suse.com>


